     1	---
     2	title: "mcp-click-up: Feature Catalog"
     3	description: "Unified reference combining the complete feature inventory and current-reality reference for the mcp-click-up skill — cupt CLI (v0.7.1+) and Official ClickUp MCP (46 tools)."
     4	version: 1.0.0.3
     5	---
     6	
     7	# mcp-click-up: Feature Catalog
     8	
     9	Complete feature inventory for both tools in the mcp-click-up skill. This catalog describes **what ships today** — not roadmap aspirations. Execution detail (exact prompts, commands, expected signals, pass/fail criteria) lives in the manual testing playbook.
    10	
    11	---
    12	
    13	## 1. OVERVIEW
    14	
    15	The mcp-click-up skill routes ClickUp work between two complementary tools:
    16	
    17	- **cupt CLI** (`pipx install cupt`) — 50 features across 10 command areas. Purpose-built for agent use: per-list status resolution, dry-run safety, offline cache, and `--json` output on 4 of its read commands (`list`, `show`, `statuses`, `teams` — not global).
    18	- **Official ClickUp MCP** (the `clickup_official` manual — `@clickup/mcp-server` launched over stdio via `npx -y`, `CLICKUP_API_KEY`/`CLICKUP_TEAM_ID` env vars, registered in `.utcp_config.json`, via Code Mode `call_tool_chain({ code: "..." })`). Covers surfaces cupt cannot reach: documents, time tracking, chat and reminders.
    19	
    20	> **Verification status (2026-07-10):** the ClickUp manual is currently unregistered in this environment (no `CLICKUP_API_KEY`/`CLICKUP_TEAM_ID`; a live `list_tools()` call returns zero `clickup_official.*` entries), and the npm package name configured in `.utcp_config.json` (`@clickup/mcp-server`) returned 404 on the public registry when checked. The last successful live inventory (2026-07) found 51 tools and confirmed **no goals/OKR, bulk-create, webhook, checklist, user-group, guest, or audit-log tools** — those capability classes are marked UNSUPPORTED on their individual cards below (Sections 12-14) rather than removed from the count, so the totals in this file still include them as documented-but-unsupported entries. See `../references/mcp-tools.md` for the reconciled, confirmed-only tool list.
    21	
    22	Routing is **operation-based**: each feature belongs to exactly one tool. See `../SKILL.md §2` for the routing pseudocode.
    23	
    24	| Metric | Value |
    25	|--------|-------|
    26	| cupt features | 50 |
    27	| Official MCP tools | 51 confirmed present + not-yet-reconciled (2026-07 `list_tools()`); catalog below still lists cards for the old assumed 46, with confirmed-absent ones marked UNSUPPORTED |
    28	| Total catalog entries | 96 (8 MCP cards marked UNSUPPORTED — not live capabilities) |
    29	| cupt install | `pipx install cupt` |
    30	| MCP server | `clickup_official` — `@clickup/mcp-server` via `npx -y`, `CLICKUP_API_KEY`+`CLICKUP_TEAM_ID` env vars, registered in `.utcp_config.json` (not the hosted OAuth server) |
    31	| MCP invocation | `clickup_official.clickup_official_<tool_name>` via Code Mode — confirm every name with `tool_info()`/`list_tools()`, do not guess |
    32	
    33	See `../feature-catalog/FEATURE-CATALOG.md` for the agent decision guide.
    34	
    35	---
    36	
    37	## 2. CUPT AUTHENTICATION & CONFIGURATION
    38	
    39	8 features covering credential setup, workspace defaults, and config management.
    40	
    41	### Interactive auth
    42	`cupt auth` — interactive wizard for OAuth or Personal API Token. Guides through token entry or browser-redirect OAuth flow.
    43	
    44	See [`cupt-authentication/interactive-auth.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-authentication/interactive-auth.md)
    45	
    46	### Direct token
    47	`cupt config --api-token pk_xxx` — set Personal API Token non-interactively. Token must start with `pk_`.
    48	
    49	See [`cupt-authentication/direct-token.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-authentication/direct-token.md)
    50	
    51	### Workspace default
    52	`cupt config --workspace-id <id>` — persist a default workspace ID for all subsequent commands.
    53	
    54	See [`cupt-authentication/workspace-default.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-authentication/workspace-default.md)
    55	
    56	### List default
    57	`cupt config --default-list <id>` — persist a default list ID.
    58	
    59	See [`cupt-authentication/list-default.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-authentication/list-default.md)
    60	
    61	### Show config
    62	`cupt config --show` — display workspace, default list, and masked auth state.
    63	
    64	See [`cupt-authentication/show-config.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-authentication/show-config.md)
    65	
    66	### Clear cache
    67	`cupt config --clear-cache` — remove all locally cached task data.
    68	
    69	See [`cupt-authentication/clear-cache.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-authentication/clear-cache.md)
    70	
    71	### Auth status
    72	`cupt status` — workspace name, user, and auth health check. Use as preflight before starting any agent workflow.
    73	
    74	See [`cupt-authentication/auth-status.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-authentication/auth-status.md)
    75	
    76	### Logout
    77	`cupt logout` — revoke stored credentials and clear the local cache.
    78	
    79	See [`cupt-authentication/logout.md`](cupt-authentication/logout.md)
    80	
    81	---
    82	
    83	## 3. CUPT TASK LISTING & FILTERING
    84	
    85	14 features covering all listing modes, date filters, tag/team filters, and output options.
    86	
    87	### List assigned
    88	`cupt list` — tasks assigned to the current user in the default workspace.
    89	
    90	See [`cupt-task-listing/list-assigned.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-task-listing/list-assigned.md)
    91	
    92	### Filter today
    93	`cupt list --today` — tasks due today only.
    94	
    95	See [`cupt-task-listing/filter-today.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-task-listing/filter-today.md)
    96	
    97	### Filter week
    98	`cupt list --week` — tasks due within the current week.
    99	
   100	See [`cupt-task-listing/filter-week.md`](../feature-catalog/cupt-task-listing/filter-week.md)
