    12	
    13	# Download File
    14	
    15	<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->
    16	
    17	---
    18	
    19	## 1. OVERVIEW
    20	
    21	Downloads a task attachment to the current directory. The selector can be a numeric index (from `cupt attach list` output) or a partial filename match.
    22	
    23	---
    24	
    25	## 2. HOW IT WORKS
    26	
    27	Downloaded file is saved with its original name in the current working directory (or `--output` path, if given). If a partial name matches more than one attachment, cupt raises an error instead of guessing — use the 1-based index from `cupt attach list`, or a substring specific enough to match exactly one file.
    28	
    29	---
    30	
    31	## 3. SOURCE FILES
    32	
    33	### Implementation
    34	
