    10	---
    11	
    12	# Skill Advisor: Feature Catalog
    13	
    14	<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->
    15	
    16	This catalog is the current inventory for the skill advisor. The package source of truth is `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/`, with adjacent OpenCode plugin docs included where the same hook/plugin ownership model applies. Each group links to per-feature files that cite the real implementation and test anchors.
    17	
    18	---
    19	
    20	## 1. OVERVIEW
    21	
    22	The catalog covers 42 features across 7 groups. Group 01 owns daemon correctness. Groups 02-03 own the index and lifecycle surface that feeds the scorer. Group 04 owns scoring. Group 06 exposes the MCP tools plus the daemon-backed CLI fallback. Groups 07-08 cover runtime integrations, OpenCode plugins and Python compatibility.
    23	
    24	> **Numbering note (gap-05).** The directory layout skips slot `05--*` between `scorer-fusion` and `mcp-surface`. This is an intentional historical reservation from initial scaffold design that marked the boundary between the core scoring pipeline (groups 01-04) and the integration layer (groups 06-08). The gap is preserved to keep spec-folder cross-reference stability across packets. Do not renumber.
    25	
    26	| Group | Count | Scope |
    27	| --- | --- | --- |
    28	| [daemon-and-freshness](../feature-catalog/daemon-and-freshness) | 7 | Watcher, lease, lifecycle, generation, trust state, rebuild-from-source, cache invalidation |
    29	| [auto-indexing](../feature-catalog/auto-indexing) | 7 | Derived extraction, sanitizer, provenance, sync, anti-stuffing, DF/IDF corpus, doc-frontmatter harvest |
    30	| [lifecycle-routing](../feature-catalog/lifecycle-routing) | 5 | Age haircut, supersession, archive handling, schema migration, rollback |
    31	| [scorer-fusion](../feature-catalog/scorer-fusion) | 6 | 5-lane fusion, projection, ambiguity, attribution, ablation, weights config |
    32	| [mcp-surface](../feature-catalog/mcp-surface) | 10 | `advisor_recommend`, `advisor_rebuild`, `advisor_status`, `advisor_validate`, stable compat entrypoint, `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_query`, `skill_graph_status`, `skill_graph_validate`, daemon-backed `skill-advisor` CLI |
    33	| [hooks-and-plugin](../feature-catalog/hooks-and-plugin) | 4 | Claude and OpenCode hooks, OpenCode plugin bridge and the `/goal` plugin |
    34	| [python-compat](../feature-catalog/python-compat) | 3 | Python CLI shim, regression suite, bench runner |
    35	
    36	Baseline numbers (remediation SHA `97a318d83`):
    37	
    38	| Metric | Value |
    39	| --- | --- |
    40	| Full-corpus top-1 accuracy | 80.5% |
    41	| Holdout top-1 accuracy | 77.5% |
    42	| UNKNOWN count | <= 10 |
