     2	name: mcp-click-up
     3	description: Routes ClickUp between cupt CLI (daily ops) and official MCP (docs, goals, bulk). Embedded install and agent safety invariants.
     4	allowed-tools: [Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain, Read, Write]
     5	version: 1.0.1.0
     6	---
     7	
     8	<!-- keywords: clickup cupt task-management work-queue time-tracking mcp -->
     9	
    10	# mcp-click-up Skill
    11	
    12	ClickUp task management via **cupt CLI** (primary) and **official ClickUp MCP** (secondary). Operation-based routing: cupt handles daily task ops, MCP handles documents, goals, and bulk operations.
    13	
    14	---
    15	
    16	## MARKDOWN FORMATTING CONTRACT — READ BEFORE ANY CLICKUP WRITE
    17	
    18	ClickUp stores the plain `description` field literally. Markdown submitted there shows up in the ClickUp UI as raw `### Heading`, `**bold**`, and `- [ ]` text. Whenever the content contains ANY markdown syntax, use the markdown-aware parameter for the operation:
    19	
    20	| Operation | Required parameter |
    21	| --- | --- |
    22	| Task create | `markdown_description` |
    23	| Task update (raw v2 API / Code Mode server) | `markdown_content` (`markdown_description` also accepted) |
    24	| Task update (claude.ai ClickUp connector) | `markdown_description` |
    25	| Document or page create | `content` plus `content_format: "markdown"` (connector pages: `"text/md"`) |
    26	| Task read-back | `include_markdown_description=true` |
    27	
    28	This contract applies identically on every surface: Code Mode (`clickup_official.clickup_official_*`), the claude.ai ClickUp connector (`clickup_create_task` and friends), and the raw ClickUp v2 REST API. Live-verified 2026-07-15 (scratch-task round trips plus a full Product Owner task export, all rendering headings, bold, dividers, and checkboxes correctly).
    29	
    30	**Push shape for a markdown artifact:** the document's H1 becomes the task `name` (drop it from the body); strip internal HTML comments and processing metadata; everything else travels verbatim.
    31	
    32	**Failure symptom:** literal `###` or `**` visible in a ClickUp task means someone used the plain `description` field. That is the defect, not a rendering bug.
    33	
    34	Worked examples: `references/mcp-tools.md` (Markdown Transport Contract + invocation patterns).
    35	
    36	---
    37	
    38	## 1. WHEN TO USE
    39	
    40	### Activation Triggers (explicit user phrases)
    41	
    42	- "clickup", "cupt", "mcp-click-up", "click up"
    43	- "manage tasks", "list tasks", "mark task done", "complete task"
    44	- "log time", "track time", "start timer", "stop timer"
    45	- "add note to task", "tag task", "show task details"
    46	- "process work queue", "process task queue"
    47	- "clickup documents", "clickup goals", "bulk create tasks"
    48	
    49	### Automatic Triggers (keyword patterns)
    50	
    51	- `cupt` appears in the request
    52	- `clickup` + any action verb (list, show, done, mark, note, time, tag)
    53	- "work queue" or "task queue" in a ClickUp context
    54	- "time tracking" or "work log" with project management context
    55	- MCP tool names: `clickup_create_task`, `clickup_get_task`, `clickup_manage_documents`
    56	
    57	### When NOT to Use
    58	
    59	- **@krodak/clickup-cli (`cu` command)** — different tool entirely; not supported by this skill
    60	- Community ClickUp MCP servers (@taazkareem/clickup-mcp-server) — use official MCP only
    61	- Direct ClickUp REST API calls (no CLI/MCP) — this skill adds no value there
    62	- Browser-based ClickUp automation (Playwright/Puppeteer) — wrong surface
    63	
    64	---
    65	
    66	## 2. SMART ROUTING
    67	
    68	### Resource Loading Levels
    69	
    70	```
    71	ALWAYS:    SKILL.md (this file)
    72	ON_DEMAND: references/cupt-commands.md    (when cupt command details needed)
    73	           references/mcp-tools.md         (when MCP tool details needed)
    74	           references/troubleshooting.md   (when error or auth issue detected)
    75	           references/INSTALL-GUIDE.md     (when setup or authentication details needed)
    76	```
    77	
    78	### Operation-to-Tool Routing Table
    79	
    80	| Operation | Primary Tool | Command | MCP Fallback |
    81	|-----------|-------------|---------|-------------|
    82	| List/filter tasks | cupt | `cupt list [--today\|--week\|--tag X]` | `clickup_search_tasks` |
    83	| Task details | cupt | `cupt show <id> [--notes]` | `clickup_get_task` |
    84	| Mark task complete | cupt | `cupt done <id> [--dry-run]` | `clickup_update_task` |
    85	| Add note/comment | cupt | `cupt note <id> "<text>"` | `clickup_manage_comments` |
    86	| Read comments | cupt | `cupt notes <id>` | `clickup_manage_comments` |
    87	| Start/stop timer | cupt | `cupt time start <id>` / `cupt time stop` | MCP time tracking |
    88	| Log time manually | cupt | `cupt time add <id> <dur>` | MCP time tracking |
    89	| Add tag | cupt | `cupt tag add <id> <name>` | `clickup_add_tag_to_task` |
    90	| Remove tag | cupt | `cupt tag remove <id> <name>` | `clickup_remove_tag_from_task` |
    91	| Task context | cupt | `cupt context <id>` | n/a |
    92	| Discover statuses | cupt | `cupt statuses <id>` | n/a |
    93	| **Documents** | **MCP only** | n/a | `clickup_create_document` |
    94	| **Goals/OKRs** | **MCP only** | n/a | goal management tools |
    95	| **Bulk create 5+** | **MCP only** | n/a | `clickup_create_bulk_tasks` |
    96	| **Webhooks** | **MCP only** | n/a | webhook management tools |
    97	| **Chat** | **MCP only** | n/a | chat tools |
    98	| **Audit logs** | **MCP only** | n/a | `clickup_get_audit_logs` |
    99	
   100	### Smart Router Pseudocode
   101	
   102	```python
   103	from pathlib import Path
   104	
   105	SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent
   106	RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / "references", SKILL_ROOT / "assets")
   107	DEFAULT_RESOURCE = "references/cupt-commands.md"
   108	# Fallback-only: DEFAULT_RESOURCE is a defer-time suggestion, never unioned
   109	# into a route's loaded set. Scored routes load exactly RESOURCE_MAP[intent];
   110	# zero-score routes load nothing and ask for disambiguation instead.
   111	DEFAULT_RESOURCE_SEMANTICS = "fallback-only"
   112	
   113	UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [
   114	    "Confirm whether the request is for cupt daily ops, official ClickUp MCP, install/auth, or troubleshooting",
   115	    "Provide the task ID, command, error text, or target ClickUp feature",
   116	    "Confirm whether cupt CLI or Code Mode MCP is already configured",
   117	    "Confirm the verification command before completing any write action",
   118	]
   119	
   120	INTENT_SIGNALS = {

codex
Three ownership boundaries are emerging: the hub catalog should describe routing behavior, the advisor catalog should describe the returned `compiledRoute` metadata, and the spec-kit governance catalog should describe the flag/kill-switch lifecycle. Child-mode and transport catalogs should not duplicate hub routing because their own catalog scopes begin after hub selection.
